  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, 1–4 m, branches spreading.  Leaves: petiole 1–3 mm; blade 3–8 cm, surfaces pilose on major veins abaxially.  Inflorescences spreading or ascending, secund, curved or recurved, 5–12 cm; bracts ± deciduous, ovate-deltate, 1–1.7 mm.  Flowers: calyx campanulate, sepals ovate, 2.5–3 mm, apex acute; corolla white to pale pink, 7–9 mm, lobes recurved, glabrous; stamens 3–4 mm; anthers 2-awned, ca. 1.5 mm, thecae divergent distally; ovary glabrous.  Capsules 3–5 mm wide.  Seeds winged, oblanceoloid, flat, 1–1.3 mm.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Flowering mid spring</description>
